Angelia: Lio, thanks for the hard work. Have you informed everybody?
Lio: Yes! When they heard that the princess is visiting the Slums in person, everyone got super excited~
Angelia: Previously, the folks at the Slums took great care of me. Now, it's my turn to repay their kindness.
Angelia: I will ensure that everyone gets to welcome a happy new year~
Naya: Speaking of which, this place is already ragged, to begin with... It has been a while since we came here; seems that it has gotten worse.
Naya: From the looks of it, a renovation will take significant time and effort...
Angelia: Naya is right. Therefore, let us begin right away!
Naya: (When was the last time I saw Angel in such high spirits...... Probably the first time since the end of the civil war.)
Sione: No matter how you look at it, if it's about the new year, then it should begin by cleaning up your surroundings.
Dylan: Closely examine the changes in the past year while cleaning, that's how you can welcome the new year with the purest attitude.
Sione: Indeed, colonel! Sione shall keep it in mind at all times!

Angelia: The last time I was here, I still knew nothing at all...

Angelia: Ah, no good, no good. I was almost caught up in my own monologue!
